  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is an extension to younger patients of the currently ongoing national,
      multicenter, open-label, randomized phase III HAPLOMUDELDERLY which evaluates elderly
      patients with hematological malignancies, justifying an allo-HSCT from an alternative donor
      when a MRD has not been identified. It will extend the investigation of these two modalities
      of allo-HSCT to younger patients which are eligible to RIC.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
